{
  "video_id": "jMVAgCPYYHY",
  "title": "What the discovery of gravitational waves means | Allan Adams",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12873.0,
      "end_time": 16790.0,
      "text": "1.3 billion years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 16104.0,
      "end_time": 19174.0,
      "text": "in a distant, distant galaxy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 19198.0,
      "end_time": 22552.0,
      "text": "two black holes locked into a spiral,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 22576.0,
      "end_time": 24655.0,
      "text": "falling inexorably towards each other"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 25234.0,
      "end_time": 26608.0,
      "text": "and collided,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 26632.0,
      "end_time": 29575.0,
      "text": "converting three Suns&#39; worth of stuff"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 29599.0,
      "end_time": 32427.0,
      "text": "into pure energy in a tenth of a second."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 33769.0,
      "end_time": 35801.0,
      "text": "For that brief moment in time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 36538.0,
      "end_time": 39949.0,
      "text": "the glow was brighter than all the stars"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 39974.0,
      "end_time": 41635.0,
      "text": "in all the galaxies"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 41659.0,
      "end_time": 43683.0,
      "text": "in all of the known Universe."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 44426.0,
      "end_time": 45814.0,
      "text": "It was a very"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 46226.0,
      "end_time": 47377.0,
      "text": "big"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 47401.0,
      "end_time": 48551.0,
      "text": "bang."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 50297.0,
      "end_time": 53111.0,
      "text": "But they didn&#39;t release their energy in light."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 53135.0,
      "end_time": 55491.0,
      "text": "I mean, you know, they&#39;re black holes."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 57229.0,
      "end_time": 62700.0,
      "text": "All that energy was pumped into the fabric of space and time itself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 62940.0,
      "end_time": 65707.0,
      "text": "making the Universe explode in gravitational waves."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 65731.0,
      "end_time": 68824.0,
      "text": "Let me give you a sense of the timescale at work here."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 69317.0,
      "end_time": 71928.0,
      "text": "1.3 billion years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 71952.0,
      "end_time": 75670.0,
      "text": "Earth had just managed to evolve multicellular life."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 76250.0,
      "end_time": 79902.0,
      "text": "Since then, Earth has made and evolved"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 79926.0,
      "end_time": 85317.0,
      "text": "corals, fish, plants, dinosaurs, people and even -- God save us -- the Internet."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 86630.0,
      "end_time": 88578.0,
      "text": "And about 25 years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 88602.0,
      "end_time": 90620.0,
      "text": "a particularly audacious set of people --"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 90644.0,
      "end_time": 96230.0,
      "text": "Rai Weiss at MIT, Kip Thorne and Ronald Drever at Caltech --"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 96470.0,
      "end_time": 97841.0,
      "text": "decided that it would be really neat"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 97865.0,
      "end_time": 100577.0,
      "text": "to build a giant laser detector"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 100602.0,
      "end_time": 102984.0,
      "text": "with which to search for the gravitational waves"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 103800.0,
      "end_time": 105259.0,
      "text": "from things like colliding black holes."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 106308.0,
      "end_time": 108414.0,
      "text": "Now, most people thought they were nuts."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 109287.0,
      "end_time": 113201.0,
      "text": "But enough people realized that they were brilliant nuts"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 113225.0,
      "end_time": 118264.0,
      "text": "that the US National Science Foundation decided to fund their crazy idea."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 118288.0,
      "end_time": 121633.0,
      "text": "So after decades of development,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 121657.0,
      "end_time": 124136.0,
      "text": "construction and imagination"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 124160.0,
      "end_time": 128144.0,
      "text": "and a breathtaking amount of hard work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 128168.0,
      "end_time": 131319.0,
      "text": "they built their detector, called LIGO:"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 131343.0,
      "end_time": 135400.0,
      "text": "The Laser Interferometer Gravitational-Wave Observatory."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 136651.0,
      "end_time": 137961.0,
      "text": "For the last several years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 137985.0,
      "end_time": 141584.0,
      "text": "LIGO&#39;s been undergoing a huge expansion in its accuracy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 141608.0,
      "end_time": 144600.0,
      "text": "a tremendous improvement in its detection ability."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 144624.0,
      "end_time": 146970.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s now called Advanced LIGO as a result."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 148116.0,
      "end_time": 150362.0,
      "text": "In early September of 2015,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 151500.0,
      "end_time": 153861.0,
      "text": "LIGO turned on for a final test run"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 153885.0,
      "end_time": 156739.0,
      "text": "while they sorted out a few lingering details."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 157978.0,
      "end_time": 162256.0,
      "text": "And on September 14 of 2015,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 162280.0,
      "end_time": 165771.0,
      "text": "just days after the detector had gone live,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 166842.0,
      "end_time": 170629.0,
      "text": "the gravitational waves from those colliding black holes"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 170653.0,
      "end_time": 172128.0,
      "text": "passed through the Earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 172977.0,
      "end_time": 175160.0,
      "text": "And they passed through you and me."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 175590.0,
      "end_time": 177611.0,
      "text": "And they passed through the detector."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 179143.0,
      "end_time": 181644.0,
      "text": "(Audio) Scott Hughes: There&#39;s two moments in my life"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 181668.0,
      "end_time": 183359.0,
      "text": "more emotionally intense than that."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 183383.0,
      "end_time": 184922.0,
      "text": "One is the birth of my daughter."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 184946.0,
      "end_time": 189330.0,
      "text": "The other is when I had to say goodbye to my father when he was terminally ill."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 190510.0,
      "end_time": 193221.0,
      "text": "You know, it was the payoff of my career, basically."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 194491.0,
      "end_time": 200146.0,
      "text": "Everything I&#39;d been working on -- it&#39;s no longer science fiction! (Laughs)"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 201416.0,
      "end_time": 205585.0,
      "text": "Allan Adams: So that&#39;s my very good friend and collaborator, Scott Hughes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 205610.0,
      "end_time": 207801.0,
      "text": "a theoretical physicist at MIT,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 207825.0,
      "end_time": 210609.0,
      "text": "who has been studying gravitational waves from black holes"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 210634.0,
      "end_time": 214162.0,
      "text": "and the signals that they could impart on observatories like LIGO,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 214187.0,
      "end_time": 216202.0,
      "text": "for the past 23 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 216892.0,
      "end_time": 220648.0,
      "text": "So let me take a moment to tell you what I mean by a gravitational wave."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 221489.0,
      "end_time": 224557.0,
      "text": "A gravitational wave is a ripple"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 224581.0,
      "end_time": 227100.0,
      "text": "in the shape of space and time."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 227468.0,
      "end_time": 229478.0,
      "text": "As the wave passes by,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 229503.0,
      "end_time": 231881.0,
      "text": "it stretches space and everything in it"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 231906.0,
      "end_time": 233650.0,
      "text": "in one direction,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 233890.0,
      "end_time": 235800.0,
      "text": "and compresses it in the other."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 235893.0,
      "end_time": 238942.0,
      "text": "This has led to countless instructors of general relativity"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 238966.0,
      "end_time": 242898.0,
      "text": "doing a really silly dance to demonstrate in their classes on general relativity."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 242922.0,
      "end_time": 245679.0,
      "text": "\"It stretches and expands, it stretches and expands.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 248800.0,
      "end_time": 250256.0,
      "text": "So the trouble with gravitational waves"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 250280.0,
      "end_time": 252898.0,
      "text": "is that they&#39;re very weak; they&#39;re preposterously weak."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 253302.0,
      "end_time": 256700.0,
      "text": "For example, the waves that hit us on September 14 --"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 256724.0,
      "end_time": 261418.0,
      "text": "and yes, every single one of you stretched and compressed"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 261442.0,
      "end_time": 263120.0,
      "text": "under the action of that wave --"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 263734.0,
      "end_time": 266638.0,
      "text": "when the waves hit, they stretched the average person"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 266663.0,
      "end_time": 269774.0,
      "text": "by one part in 10 to the 21."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 269798.0,
      "end_time": 272670.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s a decimal place, 20 zeroes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 272694.0,
      "end_time": 273860.0,
      "text": "and a one."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 275519.0,
      "end_time": 278984.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s why everyone thought the LIGO people were nuts."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 279523.0,
      "end_time": 285405.0,
      "text": "Even with a laser detector five kilometers long -- and that&#39;s already crazy --"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 285429.0,
      "end_time": 288306.0,
      "text": "they would have to measure the length of those detectors"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 289780.0,
      "end_time": 293580.0,
      "text": "to less than one thousandth of the radius of the nucleus"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 293830.0,
      "end_time": 294241.0,
      "text": "of an atom."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 294265.0,
      "end_time": 296104.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s preposterous."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 296480.0,
      "end_time": 299624.0,
      "text": "So towards the end of his classic text on gravity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 300497.0,
      "end_time": 303270.0,
      "text": "LIGO co-founder Kip Thorne"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 304508.0,
      "end_time": 307495.0,
      "text": "described the hunt for gravitational waves as follows:"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 307519.0,
      "end_time": 310670.0,
      "text": "He said, \"The technical difficulties to be surmounted"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 310694.0,
      "end_time": 313700.0,
      "text": "in constructing such detectors"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 313310.0,
      "end_time": 314296.0,
      "text": "are enormous."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 315574.0,
      "end_time": 317646.0,
      "text": "But physicists are ingenious,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 318408.0,
      "end_time": 321408.0,
      "text": "and with the support of a broad lay public,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 321972.0,
      "end_time": 324947.0,
      "text": "all obstacles will surely be overcome.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 326138.0,
      "end_time": 329657.0,
      "text": "Thorne published that in 1973,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 329682.0,
      "end_time": 333600.0,
      "text": "42 years before he succeeded."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 335149.0,
      "end_time": 336408.0,
      "text": "Now, coming back to LIGO,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 336432.0,
      "end_time": 339646.0,
      "text": "Scott likes to say that LIGO acts like an ear"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 339670.0,
      "end_time": 341248.0,
      "text": "more than it does like an eye."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 341629.0,
      "end_time": 343839.0,
      "text": "I want to explain what that means."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 343863.0,
      "end_time": 346185.0,
      "text": "Visible light has a wavelength, a size,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 346209.0,
      "end_time": 348782.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s much smaller than the things around you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 348806.0,
      "end_time": 350305.0,
      "text": "the features on people&#39;s faces,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 350329.0,
      "end_time": 353820.0,
      "text": "the size of your cell phone."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 353582.0,
      "end_time": 354789.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s really useful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 354813.0,
      "end_time": 358200.0,
      "text": "because it lets you make an image or a map of the things around you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 358440.0,
      "end_time": 360431.0,
      "text": "by looking at the light coming from different spots"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 360456.0,
      "end_time": 361607.0,
      "text": "in the scene about you."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 361631.0,
      "end_time": 363573.0,
      "text": "Sound is different."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 364111.0,
      "end_time": 367561.0,
      "text": "Audible sound has a wavelength that can be up to 50 feet long."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 367585.0,
      "end_time": 369361.0,
      "text": "And that makes it really difficult --"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 369386.0,
      "end_time": 372426.0,
      "text": "in fact, in practical purposes, impossible -- to make an image"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 372450.0,
      "end_time": 374268.0,
      "text": "of something you really care about."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 374292.0,
      "end_time": 375631.0,
      "text": "Your child&#39;s face."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 376777.0,
      "end_time": 380907.0,
      "text": "Instead, we use sound to listen for features like pitch"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 380931.0,
      "end_time": 384490.0,
      "text": "and tone and rhythm and volume"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 384730.0,
      "end_time": 387445.0,
      "text": "to infer a story behind the sounds."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 388650.0,
      "end_time": 389919.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s Alice talking."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 389943.0,
      "end_time": 391476.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s Bob interrupting."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 391500.0,
      "end_time": 392750.0,
      "text": "Silly Bob."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 393809.0,
      "end_time": 396854.0,
      "text": "So, the same is true of gravitational waves."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 397688.0,
      "end_time": 402752.0,
      "text": "We can&#39;t use them to make simple images of things out in the Universe."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 402776.0,
      "end_time": 404452.0,
      "text": "But by listening to changes"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 404476.0,
      "end_time": 407919.0,
      "text": "in the amplitude and frequency of those waves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 407943.0,
      "end_time": 411200.0,
      "text": "we can hear the story that those waves are telling."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 412224.0,
      "end_time": 413765.0,
      "text": "And at least for LIGO,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 413789.0,
      "end_time": 417986.0,
      "text": "the frequencies that it can hear are in the audio band."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 418110.0,
      "end_time": 422563.0,
      "text": "So if we convert the wave patterns into pressure waves and air, into sound,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 423121.0,
      "end_time": 425899.0,
      "text": "we can literally hear the Universe speaking to us."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 427890.0,
      "end_time": 431220.0,
      "text": "For example, listening to gravity, just in this way,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 431244.0,
      "end_time": 433934.0,
      "text": "can tell us a lot about the collision of two black holes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 433958.0,
      "end_time": 437752.0,
      "text": "something my colleague Scott has spent an awful lot of time thinking about."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 437776.0,
      "end_time": 440247.0,
      "text": "(Audio) SH: If the two black holes are non-spinning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 440271.0,
      "end_time": 442160.0,
      "text": "you get a very simple chirp: whoop!"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 442469.0,
      "end_time": 446122.0,
      "text": "If the two bodies are spinning very rapidly, I have that same chirp,"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 446146.0,
      "end_time": 447868.0,
      "text": "but with a modulation on top of it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 447892.0,
      "end_time": 450257.0,
      "text": "so it kind of goes: whir, whir, whir!"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 450281.0,
      "end_time": 454832.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s sort of the vocabulary of spin imprinted on this waveform."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 455213.0,
      "end_time": 458500.0,
      "text": "AA: So on September 14, 2015,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 458524.0,
      "end_time": 461450.0,
      "text": "a date that&#39;s definitely going to live in my memory,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 461474.0,
      "end_time": 463719.0,
      "text": "LIGO heard this:"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 463743.0,
      "end_time": 465272.0,
      "text": "[Whirring sound]"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 466416.0,
      "end_time": 471296.0,
      "text": "So if you know how to listen, that is the sound of --"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 471320.0,
      "end_time": 474534.0,
      "text": "(Audio) SH: ... two black holes, each of about 30 solar masses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 474558.0,
      "end_time": 476250.0,
      "text": "that were whirling around at a rate"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 476274.0,
      "end_time": 478815.0,
      "text": "comparable to what goes on in your blender."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 479331.0,
      "end_time": 482133.0,
      "text": "AA: It&#39;s worth pausing here to think about what that means."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 482157.0,
      "end_time": 485442.0,
      "text": "Two black holes, the densest thing in the Universe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 485466.0,
      "end_time": 487646.0,
      "text": "one with a mass of 29 Suns"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 487670.0,
      "end_time": 490457.0,
      "text": "and one with a mass of 36 Suns,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 490481.0,
      "end_time": 493154.0,
      "text": "whirling around each other 100 times per second"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 493178.0,
      "end_time": 494336.0,
      "text": "before they collide."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 494360.0,
      "end_time": 496730.0,
      "text": "Just imagine the power of that."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 496819.0,
      "end_time": 498570.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s fantastic."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 499167.0,
      "end_time": 501921.0,
      "text": "And we know it because we heard it."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 503827.0,
      "end_time": 506207.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s the lasting importance of LIGO."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 507490.0,
      "end_time": 510758.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s an entirely new way to observe the Universe"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 510782.0,
      "end_time": 512639.0,
      "text": "that we&#39;ve never had before."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 512663.0,
      "end_time": 515727.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a way that lets us hear the Universe"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 515751.0,
      "end_time": 517361.0,
      "text": "and hear the invisible."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 519496.0,
      "end_time": 521794.0,
      "text": "And there&#39;s a lot out there that we can&#39;t see --"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 522556.00000000006,
      "end_time": 524184.00000000006,
      "text": "in practice or even in principle."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 524207.0,
      "end_time": 526217.0,
      "text": "So supernova, for example:"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 526241.0,
      "end_time": 530685.0,
      "text": "I would love to know why very massive stars explode in supernovae."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 530709.0,
      "end_time": 531859.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re very useful;"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 531884.0,
      "end_time": 534228.0,
      "text": "we&#39;ve learned a lot about the Universe from them."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 534252.0,
      "end_time": 537258.0,
      "text": "The problem is, all the interesting physics happens in the core,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 537283.0,
      "end_time": 539788.0,
      "text": "and the core is hidden behind thousands of kilometers"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 539812.0,
      "end_time": 541887.0,
      "text": "of iron and carbon and silicon."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 541911.0,
      "end_time": 544215.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ll never see through it, it&#39;s opaque to light."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 544240.0,
      "end_time": 548156.0,
      "text": "Gravitational waves go through iron as if it were glass --"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 548180.0,
      "end_time": 549635.0,
      "text": "totally transparent."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 550512.0,
      "end_time": 552909.0,
      "text": "The Big Bang: I would love to be able to explore"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 552933.0,
      "end_time": 555772.0,
      "text": "the first few moments of the Universe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 555796.0,
      "end_time": 557444.0,
      "text": "but we&#39;ll never see them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 557468.0,
      "end_time": 561774.0,
      "text": "because the Big Bang itself is obscured by its own afterglow."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 562703.0,
      "end_time": 564322.0,
      "text": "With gravitational waves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 564917.0,
      "end_time": 567830.0,
      "text": "we should be able to see all the way back to the beginning."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 568425.0,
      "end_time": 570218.0,
      "text": "Perhaps most importantly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 570243.0,
      "end_time": 572681.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m positive that there are things out there"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 573300.0,
      "end_time": 574891.0,
      "text": "that we&#39;ve never seen"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 574915.0,
      "end_time": 576668.0,
      "text": "that we may never be able to see"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 576692.0,
      "end_time": 578533.0,
      "text": "and that we haven&#39;t even imagined --"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 579969.0,
      "end_time": 582358.0,
      "text": "things that we&#39;ll only discover by listening."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 583255.0,
      "end_time": 585915.0,
      "text": "And in fact, even in that very first event,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 585939.0,
      "end_time": 588985.0,
      "text": "LIGO found things that we didn&#39;t expect."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 589564.0,
      "end_time": 593550.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s my colleague and one of the key members of the LIGO collaboration,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 593790.0,
      "end_time": 596717.0,
      "text": "Matt Evans, my colleague at MIT, addressing exactly that:"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 596741.0,
      "end_time": 599951.0,
      "text": "(Audio) Matt Evans: The kinds of stars which produce the black holes"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 599975.0,
      "end_time": 601237.0,
      "text": "that we observed here"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 601261.0,
      "end_time": 603390.0,
      "text": "are the dinosaurs of the Universe."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 603630.0,
      "end_time": 606738.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re these massive things that are old, from prehistoric times,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 606762.0,
      "end_time": 609407.0,
      "text": "and the black holes are kind of like the dinosaur bones"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 609432.0,
      "end_time": 611500.0,
      "text": "with which we do this archeology."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 611740.0,
      "end_time": 613622.0,
      "text": "So it lets us really get a whole nother angle"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 613646.0,
      "end_time": 615526.0,
      "text": "on what&#39;s out there in the Universe"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 615551.0,
      "end_time": 618314.0,
      "text": "and how the stars came to be, and in the end, of course,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 618338.0,
      "end_time": 621360.0,
      "text": "how we came to be out of this whole mess."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 622304.0,
      "end_time": 623956.0,
      "text": "AA: Our challenge now"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 623980.0,
      "end_time": 627740.0,
      "text": "is to be as audacious as possible."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 627840.0,
      "end_time": 630742.0,
      "text": "Thanks to LIGO, we know how to build exquisite detectors"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 630766.0,
      "end_time": 632334.0,
      "text": "that can listen to the Universe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 632359.0,
      "end_time": 635430.0,
      "text": "to the rustle and the chirp of the cosmos."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 635890.0,
      "end_time": 639780.0,
      "text": "Our job is to dream up and build new observatories --"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 639102.0,
      "end_time": 641132.0,
      "text": "a whole new generation of observatories --"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 641157.0,
      "end_time": 643156.0,
      "text": "on the ground, in space."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 643559.0,
      "end_time": 648385.0,
      "text": "I mean, what could be more glorious than listening to the Big Bang itself?"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 648973.0,
      "end_time": 650711.0,
      "text": "Our job now is to dream big."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 651552.0,
      "end_time": 652783.0,
      "text": "Dream with us."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 652807.0,
      "end_time": 653966.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 653990.0,
      "end_time": 657513.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}